The paper deals with a fundamental problem in data analysis, namely, determining the natural dimension of a data set. This is a problem that is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper proposes a novel algorithm for addressing the issue of computing and storing all secants in large data sets, which is a problem that is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including those mentioned above. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.DS, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
